const costColumns = [
  { key: 'category', header: 'Expense' },
  { key: 'monthly', header: 'Monthly' },
  { key: 'annual', header: 'Annual' },
];

const costRows = [
  { category: 'International Insurance (65-69)', monthly: 'LKR 85,000-135,000', annual: 'LKR 1.02M-1.62M' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (70-74)', monthly: 'LKR 116,000-179,000', annual: 'LKR 1.39M-2.15M' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (75-79)', monthly: 'LKR 157,000-241,000', annual: 'LKR 1.88M-2.89M' },
  { category: 'Sri Lanka Private Hospital', monthly: 'Pay per visit', annual: 'LKR 3,000-10,000/visit' },
  { category: 'Sri Lanka Public', monthly: 'Free', annual: 'Good quality, waits' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Health Insurance for Seniors in Sri Lanka 2026 | Retirement Guide"
  description="Guide to health insurance for seniors retiring in Sri Lanka. Beaches, tea country, ancient temples, affordable living, and coverage for expats 65+."
  headline="Health Insurance for Seniors in Sri Lanka"
  subheadline="Sri Lanka offers beaches, hill country, ancient Buddhist temples, affordable living, and improving stability—an emerging retirement destination with diverse landscapes."
  heroImage="/images/countries/sri-lanka-hero-bg.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Compare Senior Plans →"
  ctaButtonHref="/go/cigna-global"
>
  <h2 id="overview">Why Seniors Choose Sri Lanka</h2>
  <p>
    Sri Lanka offers extraordinary diversity—beaches on multiple coasts, hill country tea plantations, ancient Buddhist temples, and wildlife. The country is recovering economically after 2022 crisis. Costs are very affordable, English is widely spoken, and the culture is welcoming.
  </p>

  <p>
    Colombo has best healthcare and urban amenities. Galle offers colonial fort town charm. Kandy provides hill country and cultural capital. South coast beaches (Mirissa, Tangalle) attract retirees. Each region offers distinct climate and character.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-primary-900 mb-3">Key Facts for Seniors</h3>
    <ul class="text-primary-800 space-y-2">
      <li><strong>Healthcare:</strong> Adequate; Colombo best</li>
      <li><strong>Language:</strong> Sinhala/Tamil; English widely spoken</li>
      <li><strong>Cost of Living:</strong> LKR 300,000-700,000/month (~$1,000-2,300); affordable</li>
      <li><strong>Climate:</strong> Tropical; hill country cooler</li>
      <li><strong>Character:</strong> Buddhist; diverse landscapes; tea country</li>
      <li><strong>Recovery:</strong> Economic stability improving post-2022</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <h2 id="healthcare-system">Sri Lanka Healthcare System</h2>
  <p>
    Sri Lanka has decent healthcare—better than many regional peers. Nawaloka Hospital, Lanka Hospitals, Asiri in Colombo offer good private care. Public healthcare is free and functional. Outside Colombo, quality drops but basic care available. Singapore is option for complex cases.
  </p>

  <p>
    Private healthcare is affordable by Western standards. International insurance provides access to best private facilities and Singapore evacuation if needed. Many routine procedures can be handled locally.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-2">Colombo Healthcare Hub</h3>
    <p class="text-amber-800 mb-0">
      Colombo private hospitals (Nawaloka, Lanka, Asiri) handle most medical needs well. Quality is adequate for most conditions. Singapore (4-hour flight) is evacuation option for very complex cases. Consider Colombo accessibility when choosing location.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="visa-requirements">Visa Options for Seniors</h2>
  <p>
    Sri Lanka has various options for retirees:
  </p>

  <h3>Resident Guest Visa</h3>
  <p>
    For retirees with $1,500+/month income. Two-year renewable visa. Requires proof of income, health insurance, and clean record. Straightforward for qualifying retirees.
  </p>

  <h3>Retirement Visa</h3>
  <p>
    Specific retirement visa for 55+ with pension or investment income. Leads to longer-term residence. Application through Department of Immigration.
  </p>

  <h3>Extended Tourist Visa</h3>
  <p>
    30-day ETA extendable to 6 months. Some retirees use extended tourist status while exploring permanent options.
  </p>

  <h2 id="insurance-requirements">Insurance Requirements</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance requirements for Sri Lanka:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Residence visa:</strong> Health insurance required</li>
    <li><strong>Practical need:</strong> Recommended for private hospital access</li>
    <li><strong>Singapore evacuation:</strong> Important for complex cases</li>
    <li><strong>Local option:</strong> Sri Lankan insurers available</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-2">Insurance Strategy for Sri Lanka</h3>
    <p class="text-blue-800 mb-0">
      International insurance with Asia coverage including Singapore is recommended. Local private healthcare handles most needs; Singapore backup for complex cases. Cash payment works for routine care at affordable rates.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="recommended-providers">Recommended Insurance Providers</h2>
  <p>
    For seniors in Sri Lanka, Asia coverage with evacuation works well:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={providerColumns} rows={providerRows} />

  <h3>Why These Providers Work for Sri Lanka</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Cigna Global:</strong> Good Asia network, Singapore access</li>
    <li><strong>BUPA Global:</strong> Highest entry age (79), comprehensive coverage</li>
    <li><strong>Now Health:</strong> Asia expertise, regional knowledge</li>
    <li><strong>Allianz Care:</strong> Competitive regional pricing</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Get Personalized Senior Quotes</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Compare coverage from providers that work well for Sri Lanka.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/bupa-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get BUPA Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="costs">Expected Insurance Costs</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance costs for Sri Lanka are moderate:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={costColumns} rows={costRows} />

  <h3>Cost-Saving Strategies</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Higher deductibles:</strong> Sri Lankan private care is affordable</li>
    <li><strong>Pay cash routine:</strong> Consultations LKR 3,000-5,000; very affordable</li>
    <li><strong>Asia regional:</strong> Regional rather than worldwide coverage</li>
    <li><strong>Public healthcare:</strong> Free and decent quality for basics</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="scenarios">Real-World Scenarios</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 1: British Beach Seeker, 67</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> £1,600/month pension. South coast beach lifestyle.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Resident Guest Visa. Cigna Global with Singapore evacuation.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> Cigna ~LKR 105,000/month (~£350). Tropical beaches; affordable lifestyle.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 2: Australian Buddhist, 71</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> AUD 2,500/month pension. Kandy hill country, temple visits.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> BUPA Global with comprehensive coverage. Colombo for healthcare.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> BUPA ~LKR 135,000/month (~AUD 460). Spiritual retreat; cooler climate.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 3: German History Enthusiast, 66</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> €1,400/month pension. Galle Fort, colonial architecture.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Now Health with European backup. UNESCO heritage living.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> Now Health ~LKR 95,000/month (~€290). Historic charm; beach access.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="faqs">Common Questions</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Has Sri Lanka recovered from 2022 crisis?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Improving—economy stabilizing, shortages resolved, tourism recovering. IMF program supporting recovery. Daily life is normal for expats. Fuel and power now reliable. Still some economic challenges but trajectory is positive. Good time to explore.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">How affordable is Sri Lanka?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Very affordable—among Asia most affordable destinations. Comfortable retirement possible on $1,200-1,800/month. Local food very cheap. Domestic help affordable. Rent $300-600 for nice apartment. Good value for diverse lifestyle options.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is English really widely spoken?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Yes—colonial heritage means English is common. Healthcare, business, tourism operate in English. Government services available in English. One of Asia most English-friendly countries. Daily life very manageable without local language.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">What about wildlife and nature?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Excellent—diverse wildlife including elephants, leopards, whales, and birds. National parks easily accessible. Whale watching off Mirissa. Elephant sanctuaries. Hill country scenery. Compact country makes exploring easy. Nature lovers paradise.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Ready to Compare Options?</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Get quotes from providers with Asia coverage for Sri Lanka.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/now-health" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Now Health Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-0">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This guide is for informational purposes only. Insurance requirements, visa regulations, and healthcare access rules change regularly. Always verify current requirements with Sri Lankan authorities and consult with a licensed insurance professional.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
